.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/feature_catalog/06--mcp-surface/02-advisor-status.md:21:`handlers/advisor-status.ts` returns `freshness`, `generation`, `trustState` (with `state` and optional `reason`), `skillCount`, `lastScanAt` and `laneWeights` (the canonical 5-lane configuration). Freshness vocabulary is `live / stale / absent / unavailable`. The call is fail-open: even when the daemon is absent, status returns a well-formed envelope describing the shortfall.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/feature_catalog/06--mcp-surface/02-advisor-status.md-22-
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/feature_catalog/06--mcp-surface/02-advisor-status.md-23-`readAdvisorStatus()` is strictly diagnostic. It reports stale, absent or unavailable advisor state and does not repair it. Operators should call `advisor_rebuild` when status reports stale state or when a forced rebuild is needed.
